524
00:42:10,111 --> 00:42:13,809
Rym: Which is what I use my oldest crap Kano scan for.

525
00:42:14,554 --> 00:42:21,609
Scott: And it's like the resolution is going to be high enough that you can print a copy of the document, and it's going to be very, very good.

526
00:42:23,852 --> 00:42:25,744
Scott: Or email the PDF to someone.

527
00:42:25,764 --> 00:42:26,630
Scott: It's going to be very good.

528
00:42:27,010 --> 00:42:33,230
Scott: Email the PDF to one of those fax forwarding emails, and it'll come out of a fax machine somewhere and look worse than when it started.

529
00:42:33,870 --> 00:42:37,670
Rym: But I found the image scanning on those things is not great.

530
00:42:37,811 --> 00:42:39,450
Rym: It's okay, but it's not great.

531
00:42:39,750 --> 00:42:41,130
Scott: Well, you can tweak it depending.

532
00:42:41,291 --> 00:42:43,550
Rym: But, you know, it's obviously not going to be professional.

533
00:42:44,534 --> 00:42:50,150
Scott: Yeah, it's not professional level, but it's good enough for any of the use cases a normal person has for a scanner.

534
00:42:50,792 --> 00:42:52,970
Scott: Well beyond you can scan a book with it slowly.

